title.narrative: C4D, ADVOCACY & PARTNERSHIPS

description.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners have the guidance, tools and resources for effective advocacy and partnerships on child rights issues with stakeholders., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The Eritrea Country Programme is efficiently designed, coordinated, managed, and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children.

description.narrative: During 2021, UNICEF played an instrumental role in social and behaviour change communication, serving as convener of the COVID-19 risk communication and community engagement (RCCE) committee to promote behaviours required to contain community transmission, with approximately 43,911 community education sessions conducted, reaching over 1.1 million Eritreans and257,586 peoplein border towns of Debub and Gash-Barka and islands in Northern Red Sea on COVID-19 prevention and continuity of care reached and about 27,550 people (25 per cent female) reached through the national call centre. | Status:Met | As-of Date:28/12/2021
